main event: A witness reported observing a silver spherical or disk-shaped object in the sky over Manitowoc, Wisconsin on November 6, 1953.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 1.5 minutes,It descended from the sky at high speed and made a sudden 90 degree turn,The observer described the object as appearing the size of a lead pencil eraser when viewed from the ground,The witness reported that the object remained in the same position for an extended period,The conclusion of the report noted insufficient identifying data to determine the object's nature.
sighted object: a silver spherical or disk-shaped object
witness description: Witness from the Major Civil Air Patrol with a private pilot license
